data.title: Minneapolis StarTribune
data.meta_description: Minneapolis StarTribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Henry Buslee

Buslee, Henry "Hans" beloved husband of Roxann, companion of Oslo, lost his battle with cancer on August 25, 2024 at age 70. He was preceded in death by his parents, Ruth and Henry; sister, Ingrid; nieces, Anna and Kristen. He is also survived by brother, Christopher; nephew, Tom; many grandnieces & nephews, and...

Pierre d'Albertis

Pierre Henry Louis d'Albertis, 92, Wyoming, MN, passed away peacefully on Tuesday, August 27, 2024.

Born July 16, 1932 in New York City, he was the son of Louis and Anna (Naro) d'Albertis.

Pierre d'Albertis proudly served in the United States Marine Corps as a corporal during the Korean War from 1951 to 1954. He...

Christopher Elliott

Christopher Arlen Elliott, 66, passed away on June 13, 2024 surrounded by his children and their partners.

Chris was born on August 5, 1957 to Arlen and Dorothy Elliott in Muscatine, IA. The third of four children, Chris was as quick with a bad joke as he was to wreak a little havoc; much-loved stories include cats...

Jacqueline Pedrow

Pedrow, Jacqueline Stillwater, Mn. Born March 7 1942 in Owatonna, Mn to Edward and Verna Wolesky. Survived by her husband of 58 years Paul, sons John of Stillwater, Mn, and Daniel of Vallecito, Colo, and brother Dan of Becker, Mn.

Robert Rand

Robert (Bob) Damon Rand, age 74 of Carver, MN, passed away comfortably surrounded by love in his home filled with family and friends on July 16, 2024. He fought a 10-month battle with pancreatic cancer. He is survived by his love, Sheryl; three daughters, Heather (Ken), Leila, and Jessica; daughter-in-law, Kirsten...

Norman Adair

Norm Adair, age 61 of Andover, MN, passed away on August 20, 2024. Beatrice Barager

Beatrice Josephine (Kava) Barager passed away peacefully on Saturday August 24, 2024.
